[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-28T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"2B holding something back with all her strength in a still from Nier: Automata Ver1.1a\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: SQUARE ENIX/Council of Humanity\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/28717799.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">After being left feeling deflated by the first episode of <em>Nier: Automata Ver1.1a, </em>an adaptation of the outstanding video game from Yoko Taro and PlatinumGames,<em> </em>I didn\u2019t think I\u2019d return to it.<strong> </strong>It played like what a cynic would expect: an almost one-to-one recreation but with uglier 3D animation; it felt like it was missing something. It didn\u2019t get much of a chance to make a case for itself; even with its sparks of promise, the first half of the show was plagued by <a href=\"https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2023-0", "id": 1230523, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/anime/457315/nier-automata-ver1-1a-review-good-actually", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nier: Automata Ver1.1a is the sleeper hit of the anime season", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-28T15:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A woman reaches for something under the bed while looking very scared in Sleep\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Magnet Releasing\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/5_0992ea.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Train to Busan</em>, <em>The Wailing</em>, <em>A Tale of Two Sisters</em>, <em>I Saw the Devil </em>\u2014 the Korean horror movies that have crossed over and popped in the States have been <em>intense</em>, often sprawling films that teeter on the edge of thriller. Their nightmares linger.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">So <em>Sleep</em>, now in U.S. theaters, was an immediate surprise, simply by being a Korean horror movie with a playful rhythm. Think the heightened naturalism of Bong Joon-ho\u2019s <em>Parasite </em>or <em>The Host</em>\u2026 but weirder. The feature debut of ", "id": 1230293, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/movies/457288/sleep-movie-2024-review", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sleep turns sleepwalking into a supernatural slasher \u2014 and it\u2019s wicked fun", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-28T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Alan Tudyk reacting to his alien hand in Resident Alien\" data-caption=\"Tudyk in Resident Alien, with a claw he&#039;ll (probably?) not have in Superman | Photo: SyFy / Everett Collection\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo: SyFy / Everett Collection\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/TCDREAL_SF043.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption>Tudyk in Resident Alien, with a claw he&#039;ll (probably?) not have in Superman | Photo: SyFy / Everett Collection</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Even as a diehard <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23428458/henry-cavill-superman-man-of-steel\"><em>Man of Steel </em>advocate</a>, I am excited for <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24150323/superman-costume-james-gunn-david-corenswet-underwear\">James Gunn\u2019s new take on <em>Superman</em></a>. It\u2019s the DCU\u2019s first major project since <a href=\"https://www.pol", "id": 1230294, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dc/457411/alan-tudyk-superman-movie-role-casting-who", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What is Alan Tudyk&#8217;s secret role in Superman?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-28T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Maxis/EA\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/vlcsnap-2024-09-26-16h16m33s999.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">In the opening scene of Alfred Hitchcock\u2019s <em>Rear Window</em>, a panning camera shows the outside of buildings and gives the viewer a glimpse inside the apartments. From the floating vantage point, you can see the ongoings of neighbors as they start their days. The view of the camera helps set the scene for the movie, but its voyeuristic gaze into the lives of its characters is unsettling. I\u2019m worried that playing <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/the-sims-4/12679\"><em>The Sims 4</em></a> warped me into the kind of person who looked at my neighbors like that.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As many twisted endeavors do,", "id": 1229775, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/457097/sims-4-recreating-neighborhoood", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "I started building my neighborhood in The Sims and now I feel like a creep\u00a0", "vote": 0}]